# Balatro Redux Prototype Documentation

## 1. What This Project Is

This project is a React + Redux card game prototype inspired by Balatro.

It is built around one important architectural idea:

- the game rules live in pure functions
- the UI reads state and dispatches actions
- animation and interaction state that should not permanently change the game lives locally in React

That separation is the main reason this project is understandable.

If you want to learn how to build a game in React, this is the right mental model:

1. Put permanent game rules in pure engine code.
2. Put global game state in one central store.
3. Put temporary visual state in local components or hooks.
4. Use selectors for derived values like previews.
5. Keep rendering components mostly dumb.

The project already follows that direction.

