## 6. The Main Game State

The central state shape is the run state.

Conceptually it contains:

- deck
- draw pile
- discard pile
- current hand
- selected cards
- joker list
- money
- ante
- round
- target score
- round score
- remaining hands
- remaining discards
- current blind
- shop offers
- game status
- last scoring breakdown
- status message

This state is global because many different parts of the UI need it at the same time.

Examples:

- HUD needs round score and money
- hand needs selected IDs
- play controls need whether play/discard are allowed
- shop needs offers and money
- deck viewer needs draw pile

If this state was fragmented across components, the app would become harder to reason about.

