## 7. How The Reducer Layer Works

The Redux slice is intentionally thin.

`src/store/gameSlice.ts` mostly maps Redux actions to engine functions:

- `beginRun -> startRun`
- `toggleSelectCard -> toggleCard`
- `playSelectedHand -> playHand`
- `discardSelectedCards -> discardSelected`
- `buyJoker -> buyShopOffer`
- `continueFromShop -> advanceFromShop`
- `goToMenu -> returnToMenu`

This is a good pattern.

Why?

Because the slice is not trying to contain all business logic.

Instead:

- Redux owns action wiring
- engine functions own rules

This keeps reducers cleaner and easier to test conceptually.

