## 12. Why Selectors Matter In React Game Code

Selectors are one of the most educational parts of this project.

`selectHandPreview` is a good example of how to think in React:

- raw state = selected card IDs and hand cards
- derived state = evaluated hand and preview score

The selector computes the preview when needed.

That means:

- reducer state stays smaller
- components stay cleaner
- game logic remains reusable

If you build more games in React, always ask:

"Is this value permanent game state, or is it derived from existing state?"

If it is derived, prefer a selector or pure function.

