## 17. Hand Interaction Architecture

The hand system is split into:

- `src/ui/components/Hand/Hand.tsx`
- `src/ui/components/Hand/HandCard.tsx`
- `src/ui/components/Card/Card.tsx`
- `src/ui/components/Card/cardAppearance.ts`

### `Hand.tsx`

Owns hand-level behavior:

- container ref
- drag intent suppression
- keyboard selection handling
- overlap style generation

### `HandCard.tsx`

Owns one card item in the fan:

- drag config
- motion config
- hover/tap animation
- z-index rules
- single-card render

### `Card.tsx`

Renders the face of a card only.

That is the right level of abstraction.

The card face component should not need to know about drag state or hand sorting.

### `cardAppearance.ts`

Contains visual suit-class mapping.

This is small, but it matters.

Pulling that helper out prevents the visual mapping function from living inside a render component that has a different job.

