## 19. How I Would Build A Similar Game From Scratch

If you want to recreate this later by yourself, this is the order I would follow.

### Phase 1: Model the game

Start with types only.

Define:

- Card
- Suit
- Rank
- HandEvaluation
- ScoringBreakdown
- RunState

Do not build UI first.

### Phase 2: Build the engine without React

Write pure functions for:

- deck creation
- shuffle
- draw
- hand evaluation
- scoring
- round transitions

Test these first.

If your engine is weak, the UI will become misleading and harder to debug.

### Phase 3: Add Redux or another state container

Wrap engine transitions in actions.

Keep reducer code thin.

Let the reducer call pure engine functions instead of embedding game math directly.

### Phase 4: Build selectors

Before building fancy UI, add selectors for:

- selected cards
- current blind
- hand preview
- whether actions are allowed

This gives the UI a clean API.

### Phase 5: Build the static screen

Only after the engine is stable, render:

- HUD
- hand
- controls
- shop
- score display

At this stage, do not worry about animation.

### Phase 6: Add interaction

Now add:

- selecting cards
- dragging cards
- sort buttons
- deck viewer

### Phase 7: Add experience layers

Then add:

- play telegraphing
- count-up feel
- hover motion
- screen transitions
- sound

This order matters.

Do not mix game-rule creation and animation creation at the same time if you can avoid it.

