## 20. Why This Structure Works Well For Learning

This project is useful educationally because it shows two different kinds of state.

### Permanent game state

Examples:

- money
- jokers
- round score
- draw pile
- selected card IDs

### Temporary presentation state

Examples:

- current play animation
- deck viewer visibility
- local hand order mode

Once you really understand that split, building games in React becomes much easier.

Most beginner React game code becomes messy because:

- engine state
- view state
- timing state
- animation state

all get mixed into the same component.

This project is moving away from that mistake and toward a cleaner structure.

